1. Executive Summary
1.1 Purpose

The Technical Requirements Document (TRD) defines the complete technical architecture, engineering decisions, technology stack, software components, infrastructure, security considerations, and implementation guidelines for the Developer Intelligence Platform.

Unlike conventional GitHub analytics tools that report repository statistics, this platform leverages AI to infer engineering capability, learning progression, portfolio quality, and recruiter-relevant insights from GitHub repositories and resumes.

The TRD acts as the engineering blueprint for implementation and serves as the single source of truth for system design decisions.

2. Product Overview
Vision

Build an AI platform capable of understanding developers instead of repositories.

Instead of reporting:

Number of commits
Stars
Forks
Followers

The platform should answer:

What kind of engineer is this?
What technologies does this person actually understand?
How has this developer evolved?
Are their projects production-ready?
Which engineering practices do they follow?
What skills are missing for their target career?
