11. Data Normalization

Before any AI processing, all incoming GitHub data is normalized into a consistent internal schema.

Example normalized repository object:

{
  "repository_id": "uuid",
  "name": "portfolio",
  "language": "TypeScript",
  "topics": ["react", "nextjs"],
  "readme": "...",
  "stars": 12,
  "license": "MIT",
  "has_docker": true,
  "has_tests": false,
  "deployment_detected": true,
  "last_updated": "2026-07-12"
}